Mplus VERSION 7
MUTHEN & MUTHEN
05/08/2026   2:43 AM

INPUT INSTRUCTIONS

  TITLE:
    KCYPS 2018 m1 9-item depression LCGA K=4;

  DATA:
    FILE IS kcyps_dep9.dat;

  VARIABLE:
    NAMES ARE id y1 y2 y3 y4 y5 y6 y7;
    USEVARIABLES ARE y1 y2 y3 y4 y5 y6 y7;
    IDVARIABLE IS id;
    MISSING ARE ALL (-999);
    CLASSES = c(4);

  ANALYSIS:
    TYPE = MIXTURE;
    ESTIMATOR = ML;
    STARTS = 1000 250;
    STITERATIONS = 20;
    PROCESSORS = 4;

  MODEL:
    %OVERALL%
      i s q | y1@-3 y2@-2 y3@-1 y4@0 y5@1 y6@2 y7@3;
      i@0;
      s@0;
      q@0;
      y1-y7 (resid);
    %c#1%
      [i s q];
    %c#2%
      [i s q];
    %c#3%
      [i s q];
    %c#4%
      [i s q];

  OUTPUT:
    TECH1 TECH4 TECH8;

  SAVEDATA:
    FILE IS lcga9_k4_cprob.dat;
    SAVE = CPROBABILITIES;




*** WARNING in MODEL command
  All continuous latent variable covariances involving I have been fixed to 0
  because the variance of I is fixed at 0.
*** WARNING in MODEL command
  All continuous latent variable covariances involving S have been fixed to 0
  because the variance of S is fixed at 0.
